  "number": 5523,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/5523",
  "title": "fix(insights): call `init` only if it has not been called before",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\n[FX-2272](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2272)\r\n\r\nAlternative to #5529\r\n\r\nIf `init` has already been called outside on `search-insights`, calling `init` in the insights middleware would clear the previous options and we want to avoid that behavior.\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nWe make sure `init` is called only if it has not been called before in the `sendEventToInsights` method:\r\n\r\n- First, we try to send the event.\r\n- If it fails, we catch the error, meaning that `search-insights` is not initialized yet and we `init` before sending the event.\r\n- Then, if the `search-insights` queue length has changed in the meantime, it means that `search-insights` is not yet loaded.\r\n- If `init` has not already been added to the queue, we add it and make sure to put it in the first position in the queue.\r\n\r\n> **It's just a PoC for now, don't merge!**\r\n\r\n[FX-2272]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-2272?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
